http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#com.@value: Entities ontology is the central module of the Digital Construction Ontology suite. It defines the essential top-level objects that can be referred to in construction and renovation projects by people or systems. The core concept is the ‘Identifiable Entity’, which refers the top abstract concept of all the objects that can have multiple different identifiers and can be classified according to different class classification schemes.
Def: A process that is intentionally performed by an agent.
The actors and stakeholders of construction projects.
Constituent of a construction entity with a characteristic technical function, form or position.
Minimum bounding box of an entity given by a minimum cartesian position and maximum cartesian position
Cartesian position expressed as x, y, and z coordinates with respect to a spatial origin and spatial orientation
Cartesian volume given by the lengths to x, y, and z directions
Classification enables the specification where an Identifiable Entity   belongs in a given classification scheme (such as OmniClass, UniFormat, CoClass, Talo2000, etc.)
Equipment refers to all the equipment and tool that are used for production activities. An equipment do not have a capability to operate activities by itself automatically.
Minimum bounding box of a geographical area determined by its minimum geographical position and maximum geographical position
Geographic position expressed in longitude, latitude and altitude with respect to a geographic coordinate system.
A set of indentifiable entities. Examples are a procurement package, a shipment, a workgroup, or the walls of a space.
Identifier allows the specification of a (global or local) identifier, based on the given identification system (GUID, URI, room number in a building, etc.)
Identifiable information content. Examples are a BIM model, a drawing, a specification, an image, a message, and an issue. Separate from physical information carriers.
Location refer to particular places
Material batch refers to the collection of homogeneous physical substance that participates in the construction project as the input of a process.
Orientation in two dimensions given by the orientation angle from true north
The dimensions of a spatial region
A position in a space
A quality that concerns the spatial aspects of an entity
Orientation given by three angles: angle about x-axis (alpha), angle about y-axis(beta) and angle about z-axis (gamma)
TimeInstant
TimeInterval
Orientation of a plane in two dimensions given by its angle about true north (the strike) and the angle of its slope (the dip)
A machine used for transporting goods in construction process
